# Semgrep ignore list — TrustedOSS Portal
#
# Each entry must be either a glob pattern (one per line) or a comment.
# We use this for non-product material that semgrep happens to scan but
# whose findings cannot be acted on (agent definitions, sample snippets,
# generated artifacts).

# Claude Code agent definitions ship runnable-looking code samples that are
# documentation, not deployable code. Treating them as product would force
# every snippet to satisfy production hardening rules.
.claude/

# Documentation site source — Markdown / MDX with code samples.
docs/

# Generated bundles / build outputs.
dist/
build/
node_modules/
.venv/
__pycache__/
